a:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"M5 SoC sips 7-8W in *Cyberpunk 2077* on passive cooling"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"No fans, no throttling—but at what performance cost?"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Gamers split: ‘Finally!’ vs. ‘Still not a gaming laptop’"}]]}]]}]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["Apple’s new ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.apple.com/macbook-air-m5/","children":"MacBook Air M5"}]," just pulled off a magic trick: running ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Cyberpunk 2077"}]," and ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Baldur’s Gate 3"}]," while sipping ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"7-8 watts"}]," of power, according to ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.notebookcheck.net/Apple-s-M5-MacBook-Air-consumes-just-7-8W-while-gaming.765432.0.html","children":"NotebookCheck’s tests"}],". That’s less than a nightlight—and somehow, it’s ",["$","em",null,{"children":"not"}]," melting into a puddle of thermal paste. The secret? A passive-cooled, entry-level M5 SoC that refuses to throttle itself into oblivion like so many ultrabooks before it.\nFor laptop gamers, this is the equivalent of finding out your ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://store.steampowered.com/steamdeck","children":"Steam Deck"}]," runs on hamster wheels and still beats your buddy’s RTX 4090 in efficiency. The ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"COMMUNITY PULSE"}]," is already split: Reddit’s r/MacGaming is half ‘",["$","em",null,{"children":"finally, a laptop that doesn’t sound like a jet engine"}],"’ and half ‘",["$","em",null,{"children":"lol 30 FPS in 720p isn’t gaming"}],".’ But here’s the thing—this isn’t about raw power. It’s about ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"what you can actually play, where you can actually play it"}],".\nThe M5 Air isn’t pretending to be an ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.dell.com/en-us/shop/gaming-laptops/alienware-m18-gaming-laptop/spd/alienware-m18-laptop","children":"Alienware m18"}],". It’s a 13-inch ultrabook that runs ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Baldur’s Gate 3"}]," on a park bench without setting your lap on fire. That’s a ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"PLAYER EXPECTATION"}]," shift: no more ‘",["$","em",null,{"children":"I’ll just plug in when I get home"}],"’—this is ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Cyberpunk"}]," on a café’s dodgy Wi-Fi, and it ",["$","em",null,{"children":"works"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/macbook-air-m5-gaming-is-a-7w-miraclewith-a-catch/subtitle.jpg","alt":"When your ‘ultrabook’ outlasts your desktop’s power bill","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"When your ‘ultrabook’ outlasts your desktop’s power bill"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["But let’s talk ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"BACKLASH RADAR"}],", because of ",["$","em",null,{"children":"course"}]," there’s friction. The M5’s efficiency is impressive, but it’s still an ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"entry-level"}]," chip. Early benchmarks suggest it’s roughly on par with an ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.anandtech.com/show/17015/the-apple-m1-pro-and-m1-max-review/4","children":"M1 Pro"}],"—which means you’re looking at ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"medium settings, 1080p, and 40-60 FPS"}]," in most modern titles. Not exactly a ‘",["$","em",null,{"children":"max everything and forget"}],"’ experience. Steam Deck owners might scoff, but here’s the kicker: the Air’s ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"battery life"}]," while gaming is reportedly ",["$","em",null,{"children":"hours"}]," longer than any x86 ultrabook daring to try the same.\nThe real question isn’t ",["$","em",null,{"children":"can"}]," it game—it’s ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"who is this for?"}]," The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.reddit.com/r/pcmasterrace/","children":"r/pcmasterrace"}]," crowd will dismiss it as ‘","$L13","’ (and they’re not wrong). But for the ","$L14","* crowd? This is a revelation. No fans. No bulk. No ‘","$L15","’ YouTube tutorials. It’s the first time a MacBook has genuinely competed in the ‘","$L16"," conversation since… well, ever.\nThat said, ","$L17"," check: NotebookCheck’s tests are solid, but we’re still waiting for wider real-world reports. If this holds up, Apple’s just redefined what ‘casual gaming’ looks like—","$L18"," by brute-forcing performance, but by making it ","$L19","."]}]]}]
